                                    <!-- FAQ Section for AEO -->
                                    <div class="faq-section" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                                        <h3>How much cheaper is app development in India compared to the USA?</h3>
                                        <p>Roughly 4-5x cheaper for senior engineering talent. A USA-priced $200k MVP runs $42k-$72k in India for the same scope. After project management overhead, the net savings are 70-78%.</p>
                                        <h3>Is the quality of Indian app developers comparable to US developers?</h3>
                                        <p>The top 15% of Indian engineers match US senior-level quality. The middle 50% match US mid-level. The bottom 35% (freelancers and body-shops) are below US junior level. Vet the studio, not the country.</p>
                                        <h3>How much faster do Indian agencies typically deliver?</h3>
                                        <p>Same scope: India top-tier ships in 8-14 weeks vs US agency 14-22 weeks. The reason: leaner discovery process, fewer stakeholder layers, larger parallel team for the same dollar budget.</p>
                                        <h3>What's the total cost of ownership including overheads?</h3>
                                        <p>Add 5-8% to India quotes for PM and timezone overhead, ~2% for compliance setup. Add 12-18% to US quotes for benefits load on FTEs. Net: India remains 3.5-4.2x cheaper after all overheads.</p>
                                        <h3>Can I save money by hiring Indian freelancers directly on Upwork?</h3>
                                        <p>Possible for very small projects (under $5k), but failure rates exceed 60% for production-grade apps. The labour-cost saving versus an Indian studio is 30-40%, but you absorb all PM, QA and architecture risk yourself. Most founders try this once, then move to studio.</p>
